	(text "CHEMIN B — JE-990 DIY (Deane Jensen, 1980)\n\nSTAGE 1: Differential Input\n  Q1B/Q2B (AS394H matched NPN pair)\n  R1B/R2B = 30R emitter degeneration\n  L1B/L2B = 22µH emitter inductors (Jensen innovation)\n  Q4B (2N3904) tail current source, R3B = 160R\n\nSTAGE 2: Active Load / Cascode\n  Q3B (2N4250A PNP) active load Q1\n  Q5B (2N4250A PNP) active load Q2\n  CR3 (1N4148) bias reference\n  R4B/R5B = 300R collector loads\n\nSTAGE 3: VAS\n  Q6B (2N4250A PNP) voltage amplifier\n  C1B = 150pF Miller compensation (CRITICAL)\n  R7B = 160R, R8B = 130R\n\nSTAGE 4: Output Push-Pull Class-AB\n  Q8B (MJE181 NPN) + Q9B (MJE171 PNP)\n  Q7B (2N3904) PNP pre-driver\n  R13B = 3.9R current sense\n  R14B/R15B = 39R output degeneration\n  C2B = 62pF, C3B_comp = 91pF HF compensation\n  CR1-CR12 (1N4148) protection + bias\n\nOUTPUT:\n  Load Isolator: R_loadB(39R/1W) wound with L3B(40T #30)\n  C_outB(220µF bipol + 4.7µF film) → OUTPUT_B\n\nFEEDBACK:\n  Output → SW1 Pole B (Rfb) → (-) input\n  Rg_B = 47R (0.1%) to GND\n  Gain = 1 + Rfb/47"
		(at 25.4 25.4 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.524 1.524)) (justify left))
		(uuid "f5000001-j990-text-0005-000000000001")
	)
)
